cs.CV, cs.CL, cs.IR, cs.MM, cs.LG 

The paper deals with the problem of discovering links between images and sentences in multi-image multi-sentence documents. This involves tasks related to computer vision (image analysis), natural language processing (sentence analysis), information retrieval (finding relevant information), multimedia (dealing with multiple modalities), and machine learning (developing algorithms to learn from data). Therefore, the most likely arXiv CS sub-category is cs.CV (Computer Vision and Pattern Recognition), followed by cs.CL (Computation and Language), cs.IR (Information Retrieval), cs.MM (Multimedia), and cs.LG (Machine Learning).
